AUTHOR: Poli

QUALIFICATION: Humphrey ms; in syn. (Moore); G.B. Sowerby II (1842, A conchological manual, ed. 2: 168) has an entry for Lacinea Humphrey. Not available under Art. 11.5.2: listed in a dictionary as equal to Chama Lamarck [Chama Linnaeus, 1758], but not used as the valid name of a taxon.
AUTHOR: Sowerby II

QUALIFICATION: Humphrey ms; Neave, Nomenclator Zoologicus, has an entry for Gryphus Gray [ex Humphreys MS] 1847, Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 15: 193. However, Gray merely cited Gryphus Humph. MSS. 1797 in the synonymy of Chama. It is not an available name

QUALIFICATION: Bouchet lists the valid name 'Lamarck [ex Leach MS] 1818 Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertèbres, 5: 543; Introduced in synonymy, but treated as valid before 1960. Mysia T. Brown, 1827 [Illustrations of the conchology of Great Britain and Ireland: pl. 16] and Mysia Wood, 1840 [The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6: 250] are listed by Sherborn and Neave as separate names. In the index (p. ii), Brown attributed Mysia to Leach, and Wood also refered to Leach, so it is clear that both Lamarck, Brown and Wood used the same name, although with different taxonomic extensions; Tellina rotundata Montagu [Ungulinidae] was the only species included in Mysia by Brown, and Wood included Mysia ornata Wood, 1840 and Venus undata
